column26: Illumina HiSeq 2000 sequencing; Strobilurins as growth-promoting compounds: How Stroby regulates Arabidopsis leaf growth
column27: Strobilurins as growth-promoting compounds: How Stroby regulates Arabidopsis leaf growth
column28: Illumina HiSeq 2000 sequencing; Strobilurins as growth-promoting compounds: How Stroby regulates Arabidopsis leaf growth
column29: Protocols: Seeds were stratified and germinated in soil for three days in the presence or absence of Stroby, after which they were watered twice a week with or without Stroby until 17 DAS. Plants were grown in soil at 21 ̊C under a 16-h day (80-100 µmol m-2 s-1) and 8-h night regime.  Stroby® WG (BASF), a commercially available strobilurin consisting of 50% (w/w) KM as active ingredient and 50% surfactants, was dissolved in water and used as source of KM at a concentration of 10-9 M. Library preparation was done using the TruSeq RNA Sample Preparation Kit v2 (Illumina). Briefly, polyA-containing mRNA molecules were reverse transcribed, double-stranded cDNA was generated and adapters were ligated. After quality control using a 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent), clusters were generated through amplification using the TruSeq PE Cluster Kit v3-cBot-HS kit (Illumina). RNA was extracted using Trizol (Invitrogen) and the RNeasy Plant Mini Kit (Qiagen)
